                            <comment id="102695" author="simmonsja" created="Tue, 6 Jan 2015 22:17:58 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I have done exhaustive testing and looked very closely at the what states lustre procfs handling is in for the case of client and server being on the same node.  I loaded lod then lov and vice versa as well as unload the modules in the two possible orders. I detected no leaks in either case. In order to fill out out proc trees we have to preform mounting/unmounting of the MDT and the client. I tried both orders of mounting and&lt;br/&gt;
umount and saw no issues with remove_proc_subtree. Tired various combos of mounting/unmounting and module loading/unloading. No memory leaks/disappearing directories or handling symlinks occurred. Please note this is all done on a 3.12 kernel. Also looking at detail of the procfs initialization and removal don&apos;t show a issue with remove_proc_subtree. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
